  A huge badass zombie begins to cast a spell<br>
  YOUR skin fries and goes away for WAYY too much dmg.<br>
  Loading...<br>
  (Me) ARRRRRRG *kicks nearest object, probley table*<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/unefariusgnome.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nefarius Gnome</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Conjurer</span><br>  Posts: 137<br> <font color=#333333>(10/16/00 7:28:59 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerrants.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=38.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: YEAH!</span><hr size=1> I've heard that NPCs get a saving throw vs your invis. The higher level they are in relation to you, the greater their chance of seeing you. Don't know if this is true or not, but it sounds about right.<br>
<br>
Also, Kithicor is chancy with invis anyway. The undead can see through regular invis, and the wolves can see through invis vs. undead. <p><p><font face="Arial" COLOR="blue" size="2"><b>Nefarius Frobozz</b><br>Devout Agnostic Gnome Magician of the 32nd Trial<i><br>Terris-Thule<br></i></p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> aquamini</span><br> <span class=usertitle>Unregistered User</span><br>   <font color=#333333>(10/21/00 11:52:51 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerrants.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=38.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   divination..whatever..</span><hr size=1> I can deal with invis fading but when the spell is cast and i see that it is on me. I expect it to work on all mobs. I would understand if it was a caster mob and they cast see invis on themselves but they dont. I seen drachnids spawn and they only cast shields and sow on themselves but yet they can see me just fine in invis mode. non casters like tundra yetis and MGs can see me. It seems that it only works against green cons. I would be one messed up coward mage if i was scared of green cons. The blue cons see me no matter what i do so invis spell is all but useless in my travels. As for Kithicor, forget about runing thru at night even if i paid for  invis vs undead it still wouldnt work. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerrants.showPrevMessage?topicID=38.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerrants.showNextMessage?topicID=38.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerrants.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=38.topic&index=4><img src=http://ww